<HEAD>Two Sentenced In Chihuahua Death.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two men were sentenced to four to 12 months in jail for stomping a neighbor's pet <LOCATION> Chihuahua </LOCATION> to death. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Goff </PERSON>, 22, and <PERSON> Shawn </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerr </PERSON>, 19, both of nearby Imperial, were also ordered Thursday to spend five years on probation and 100 hours doing community service work for the <ORGANIZATION> Animal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rescue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pennsylvania </ORGANIZATION>. The group takes in stray dogs and cats and tried to find homes for them. Both men said they were sorry and embarrassed they stole Co-Co, a dog belonging to <PERSON> Olive </PERSON> <PERSON> Marie </PERSON> <PERSON> Maximonvich </PERSON> of Imperial. <PERSON> Goff </PERSON> and <PERSON> Kerr </PERSON> said they were drunk when they jumped into the <PERSON> Maximonvich </PERSON> family's fenced yard, tossed the animal into the street, took it to a nearby garage and stomped it to death. The dog's corpse later was burned over an open fire. Both men pleaded guilty to theft, cruelty to animals and criminal conspiracy.
