<HEAD>Australian Imported Sheep `Aloof,' Dislike Malaysia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sheep imported from <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> do n't like <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION> and refuse to crossbreed with the local species, an agricultural official said today. <PERSON> Osman </PERSON> <PERSON> Ismail </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Jempol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Area </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farmers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>, said his statements were based on the group's observation of 110 imported ewes, mostly from <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>, that were reared throughout last year Although the ewes were fed well and fertile, they were `` aloof'' and only one lamb was born to the flock, <PERSON> Ismail </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Ismail </PERSON> spoke at the group's annual general meeting at <LOCATION> Serting </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hilir </LOCATION>, 72 miles south of <LOCATION> Kuala </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lumpur </LOCATION>, the national news agency <ORGANIZATION> Bernama </ORGANIZATION> reported.
