<TEXT>
 `` Blasphemy is not the issue here, but censorship. ... But complaining of a heathen plot against the faith is good box office for the television pulpit. The would-be censors seek to shift attention away from the capers of <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Swaggart </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> and <PERSON> Tammy </PERSON> <PERSON> Bakker </PERSON>. The television preachers need to clean up their own blasphemous act first.'' _ The <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Globe </ORGANIZATION>.
