<HEAD>Leader Of Boy Sex Ring Once A Teen Prostitute Himself, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man who was once a teen-age prostitute has been charged with running an eight-year-old sex ring that sold the services of hundreds of boys, sometimes flying them to other cities, police said. Accused ringleader <PERSON> Wesley </PERSON> <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, 26, earned a living from prostitution from age 12 to 16, eventually giving it up to start the pedophile ring eight years ago, said Detective <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Sheehan </PERSON>. The Tampa-based operation came to light when the parents of an 11-year-old contacted police after wondering how their son got large amounts of cash. A four-month probe led to the arrests of <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON> and two other Floridians in June, police disclosed Wednesday. The investigation continues, and authorities say they expect more arrests in other cities. For eight years, the network sent boys to <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Indianapolis </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> to meet adult clients, said <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> Sgt. <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Reynolds </PERSON>. <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, an unemployed avionics technician, understood the psyche of the boys he hired _ most of them from poor families and broken homes _ because he was once one of them, <PERSON> Sheehan </PERSON> said. He used boys to recruit others, flashing wads of cash as a lure, <PERSON> Sheehan </PERSON> said. `` A lot of the kids despised the sex, but the financial inducements were too enticing to the youngsters,'' said <PERSON> Sheehan </PERSON>. The underground child prostitution operation involved hundreds of youths ages 11 to 16, who earned from $ 300 to $ 700 for a single meeting, police said. Getting the boys to admit their activities was difficult because of a quiet bond between them, and officials said that slowed the investigation. `` The members' loyalty stood even when faced with prison,'' <PERSON> Sheehan </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, also known as <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, was arrested in June on a <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> warrant charging him with capital sexual battery, procuring children under 16 for prostitution and deriving financial support from prostitution, according to <PERSON> Sheehan </PERSON>. He is being held without bond. The others arrested were identified as car salesman <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorman </PERSON>, 38, and <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Leroy </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>, 30, who works for a paint company. <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> was charged with lewd and lascivious acts with a child; <PERSON> Gorman </PERSON> was charged with performing a sexual act with a child. Both were released on bond.
