<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A reputed drug kingpin in prison and 36 other people, including his parents, wife and girlfriend, were charged with running a narcotics cartel linked to the assassination of a police officer and nine other murders. <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> `` Fat Cat'' <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON>, serving a 25-years-to-life sentence for state narcotics and weapons law violations, was accused of controlling the $ 20-million-a-year organization through his lieutenants and family members. According to a federal complaint released Thursday, <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON> continued to direct his drug operations from jail. `` This is really a story of how a handful of women kept this drug operation together while their men were in prison,'' said Sgt. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> McGuiness </PERSON>. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Fox </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> office, described the <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON> group as `` the most active and most vicious drug ring in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>.'' Thirty people _ including <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON>' parents, sister, three nieces, wife, girlfriend and brother-in-law _ were arrested in a sweep Thursday. Others were arrested out of state, said police spokesman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Gallagher </PERSON>. They were charged with distributing heroin and cocaine. No murder charges were filed. But the federal complaint stated that members of the <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON> organization are suspected in at least 10 narcotics-related homicides since 1985, including that of police Officer <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Byrne </PERSON> and <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON>' parole officer, <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Rooney </PERSON>, in 1985. <PERSON> Byrne </PERSON> was shot execution-style in February as he sat in his police cruiser, guarding the home of a drug witness. `` The death of O