 Democrat <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> said today that overspending by the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration is to blame for interest-rate increases that will raise the federal deficit $ 15 billion and impose hardships on families, farmers and businesses. The Democratic presidential nominee, speaking to a breakfast gathering at the <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> governor's mansion, said interest rates would continue to rise `` if we continue to live on a credit card.'' `` As we all know, sooner or later the bill collector comes to the door,'' <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> said. `` That's what happened yesterday in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>.'' He was referring to an increase in many banks' prime lending rates. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> has been criticized in <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> because he opposes construction of two new <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> supercarrier task forces which would be built at the <ORGANIZATION> Newport </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, shipyard. Gov. <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Baliles </PERSON>, who introduced <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, said he disagreed with <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> on that point but did not question his commitment to a strong national defense. `` Gov. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> and I may debate the individual choices we must make, but in his commitment to the security of this nation I have no doubts, no reservations and no hesitations,'' <PERSON> Balile </PERSON> said. Also today, <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> aides said his campaign would run a one-minute advertisement this weekend in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> and in the <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> area. The ad, <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>' first since the primary campaign, stresses his major themes, such as economic revival, and contains footage fr