/PERSON>, who was shot in the head, remains confined to a wheelchair and has difficulty speaking as a result of the injuries he suffered. Hospital officials had not formally outlined its specific plan for the outing. But court records indicate the field trip may be a picnic or a party at a bowling alley. The hospital dropped a request in April 1987 to allow <PERSON> Hinckley </PERSON> to visit his parents during the Easter weekend after investigators turned up evidence he had traded letters with multiple murderer <PERSON> Theodore </PERSON> <PERSON> Bundy </PERSON>, who is held on <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s death row. A psychiatrist testified last year that <PERSON> Hinckley </PERSON> also had once received a letter from <PERSON> Lynette </PERSON> `` Squeaky'' <PERSON> Fromme </PERSON>, who is imprisoned for trying to kill President <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> in 1975. <PERSON> Hinckley </PERSON>'s correspondence with <PERSON> Bundy </PERSON> and other writings seized from his room last year remain under court seal.
