ON> for the Total Independence of <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>, is not a party to the cease-fire. `` It would be ironical if Resolution 435 -LRB- the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> independence plan for <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION> -RRB- should reach the point of implementation only to be obstructed or made impossible as a result of provisions in the American legislation,'' <PERSON> Botha </PERSON> said. He said unspecified financial transactions necessary to implement the plan could be affected by the sanctions bill.
