untry and to give more power to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> on the international political scene. `` Even after the war, defense will continue and members of the armed forces and volunteers must be present to defend <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s territorial integrity alongside the country's reconstruction,'' he told the throng of worshipers Worshipers chanted `` Down with the U.S.A.!'' `` Down with the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>!'' and `` Down with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>!'' and pledged to obey revolutionary patriarch <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruhollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>. The audience at <PERSON> Khamenei </PERSON>'s sermon included about 100 Iraqi prisoners of war, with about 25 of them wearing red headbands indicating they want to fight Iraqi President <PERSON> Saddam </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON>. The crowd was smaller than that at a similar sermon attended by an <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> reporter four weeks ago. An official at the prayer service said the crowd was small `` because so many people have followed the call to go to the battle front.'' He spoke on condition of anonymity. Plastic collection boxes were on hand at the sermon for worshipers to contribute to the war effort. Since <ORGANIZATION> Iran </ORGANIZATION> announced it was accepting the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> cease-fire resolution, the once all-pervasive slogan `` War, war until victory!'' has been abandoned, said a Westerner based in <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> said a four-member team of chemical weapons experts would travel to the northwestern Kurdish town of <LOCATION> Oshnaviyeh </LOCATION> in the province of <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Azerbaijan </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION