. `` We have daily inspections, and we've sent people home if they do n't pass,'' <PERSON> Parker </PERSON> said. `` If they need to change their trousers or get a haircut, they go home and make up for it on their own time.'' <PERSON> Parker </PERSON> is an instructor at the <LOCATION> Ocean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> police academy, and said he teaches his classes that `` 90 percent of an officer's effectiveness is determined by his uniform If he looks sharp and feels proud, all he really needs is some voice control and a sense of personal control.'' Even if a community can not afford fancy uniforms, `` you can still look sharp. A uniform can still be creased, be clean and shoes can always be shined,'' he said. <PERSON> Lepper </PERSON> said the manufacturers assocation evaluates entrants on image projection, ease of identification, reflection of the department's authority and professionalism, practicality and protection from weather and physical attacks. The police departments also are scrutinized on how carefully they follow through on their dress code, he said. `` The single most important thing is that a police department must have consistency,'' he said. `` We want every police officer to look the same.'' The judges included a master tailor, a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> police lieutenant and the publisher of Law and Order, a police magazine. The 56-year-old uniform association represents textile mills, uniform manufacturers, dealer distributors and accessory manufacturers, <PERSON> Lepper </PERSON> said. It also sponsors annual awards for the best-dressed high school or college band, and the Image of the Year awards, which includes uniforms from car rental agencies, airlines, real estate agencies and other companies. `` A police officer's uniform is extremely important,'' <PERSON> Lepper </PERSON> said. `` When someone has an auto accident or has been mugged or assaulted, it's very comforting to see a police officer's uniform.'' `` Of course, it's different if you're getting a parking ticket,'' he joked.
