pattern of segregation. Each councilman was fined $ 500 daily. The city was fined $ 100 a day, with fines to double daily. By the 22nd day of the fines, the city would face the total elimination of its $ 337 million budget. But a three-judge appeals panel stayed the fines pending a full hearing on the contempt order next week. <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> said he wanted to await the outcome of the appeals court before taking any action. To remove elected officials is a lengthy process, he observed. Earlier this week, the <ORGANIZATION> Yonkers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Emergency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION>, imposed to oversee city spending four years ago as a condition of a bailout to stave off bankruptcy, assumed the reins of city spending. It could find the officials in violation of the control board act and set into motion a removal process, said <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON>. However, he stopped short of saying it would.
