<TEXT>
 Retail sales climbed 0.5 percent in July, the third consecutive monthly increase, the government has reported, but economists say rising interest rates threaten to dampen even this modest growth rate in the months ahead. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday that sales increased $ 632 million last month to a seasonally adjusted $ 134.0 billion.
