<HEAD>Cash Management Bills Yield 7.73 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> has auctioned 248-day cash management bills at an average discount rate of 7.73 percent. The discount rate in Thursday's auction understates the actual return to investors _ 8.19 percent with a $ 10,000 bill selling for $ 9,467.50. A total of $ 7.0 billion in bills with a minimum denomination of $ 10,000 were sold out of bids totaling $ 25.7 billion. The bills will be repaid on April 20, 1989 and are being sold to help smooth government revenue flows, which normally surge in April as people pay their income taxes.
