</LOCATION>'s five major bullion dealers fixed a recommended price for gold this morning of $ 428.40 a troy ounce, up slightly from late Thursday's bid $ 428. Trading was very quiet. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, the bid price for gold was $ 428.70, little changed from $ 428.65 late Thursday. Earlier, in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold fell 80 cents to close at a bid $ 430.99. Silver was quoted in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> today at a bid price of $ 6.75 a troy ounce, up from Thursday's $ 6.70.
