<HEAD>Six Plead Innocent In Wall Street Racketeering Case</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN M. DOYLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Five top officers of an investment group pleaded innocent to racketeering charges alleging a scheme to sell bogus stock and securities, and their lawyers criticized what they called a `` broad attack on Wall Street.'' A sixth defendant, a former trader for <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, did not attend the arraignment Thursday at federal court in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION>, but his lawyer entered an innocent plea for him. The six were named last week in a 35-count indictment on charges of racketeering and conspiracy, the first time racketeering charges have been leveled against individual securities traders. In court Thursday, prosecutors disclosed that they plan to bring a new and broader indictment in the case within two months. The indictment could add additional charges or new defendants. The defendants from <ORGANIZATION> Princeton-Newport </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, a limited partnership based in <LOCATION> Princeton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Newport </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, are <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Sutton </PERSON> <PERSON> Regan </PERSON>, 46, of <LOCATION> Pennington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>; <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Z. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rabinowitz </PERSON>, 41, <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Zarzecki </PERSON>, 40, and <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Berkman </PERSON>, 41, all of <LOCATION> Princeton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>; and <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Smotrich </PERSON>, 33, of <LOCATION> Belle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Meade </LOCATION>, <PERSON> N.J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Newberg </PERSON>, 31, of <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Monica </LOCATION>, <LOCAT