<HEAD>AT&amp;T To Offer Karmarkar Algorithm Commercially</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said Friday it was offering a computer-based system for solving business problems that is based on a formula invented in 1984 by <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Laboratories </ORGANIZATION> mathematician <PERSON> Narendra </PERSON> <PERSON> Karmarkar </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T said the system would cost $ 8.9 million, including free training, and would be ideal for customers such as airlines and companies in the process industries, such as oil, chemicals and paper. The Karmarkar algorithm greatly speeds up the solution of mathematical problems that involve the interaction of thousands of variables. It was originally used to help <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T plan the growth of its phone network. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T said an airline, for example, could use the system to improve the efficiency of its routing system, including the scheduling and allocation of planes and crews. Chemical companies could use it to balance the input of raw materials and the output of final products, <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T said. The system, known as Korbx, is being offered by a new <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> unit, <ORGANIZATION> Advanced </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Decision </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Support </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Whippany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J </LOCATION>. Some systems, but fewer than 10, have been sold, said the new unit's president, <PERSON> Aristides </PERSON> <PERSON> Fronistas </PERSON> The Karmarkar algorithm traces a path inside the `` region'' of all potential solutions to a problem until it arrives at the best one. An algorithm is simply a rule of thumb, or a special method for solving a certain kind of problem. <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Laboratories </ORGANIZATION> received three patents related to the Korbx system in May.
